[Oil]
price=1
weight=1
short=10
med=30
long=50
type=fire
stat=dex
desc=A flask of oil can be used as a grenade-like missile. The oil must be set afire in order to inflict damage; otherwise the oil is just slipepry. Assuming some means of igniting the oil is at hand, a direct hit to a creature deals 1d8 points of fire damage, plus in the next round the target takes an additional 1d8 points of damage. If the oil is ignited by some sort of wick or fuse, then all other creatures within 5 feet of the point of impact receive 1d6 points of fire damage from the splash. A save vs. Death Ray is allowed to avoid this damage.//A flask of oil spilled or splattered on the ground will burn for 10 rounds. Those attempting to cross the burning oil will receive 1d6 points of damage each round they are in it (with no saving throw in this case).

[HolyWater]
price=10
weight=0
short=10
med=30
long=50
type=holy
stat=dex
desc=Holy water is harmful to undead creatures. A character may throw a flask of holy water as a grenade-like missile, which will break and release the contents if thrown against the body of a corporeal creature. To use it against an incorporeal creature it must be opened and poured or splashed onto the target, requiring the attacker to be directly adjacent to it.//Each flask of holy water can inflict 1d8 points of damage to such a monster. In addition, each additional undead monster within 5 feet of the point of impact receives 1d6 points of damage from the splash. Holy water is only effective for one round.

[Backpack]
price=4
weight=0
desc=A backpack will hold a maximum 40 pounds or 3 cubic feet of goods. Some items may be lashed to the outside, and thus count toward the weight limit but not the volume limit.

[BeltPouch]
price=1
weight=0
desc=Belt pouches are typically used for holding small items, such as oil, holy water, potions, or sling bullets, to keep for quick use. Belt pouches can hold 1/4 cubic feet of volume and 2 pounds of weight.

[Bitandbridle]
price=0.15
weight=3
type=gear
desc=A bit is the device which the reins are tied to that is put into a horse's mouth. It is also held on the horse's head with leather straps called the bridle.

[Candles]
price=1
weight=0
type=gear
desc=A candle will shed light over a 5' radius, with dim light extending 5' further. A normal candle will burn about 3 turns per inch of height.

[Chalk]
price=2
weight=0
type=gear
desc=Chalk is useful for "blazing a trail" through a dungeon or ruin.

[Cloak]
price=2
weight=1
type=gear
desc=Cloaks are useful for camoflauge as well as avoiding harsh weather.

[CommonClothing]
price=4
weight=1
type=gear
desc=Common sewn clothing you might find on any villager.

[GlassBottle]
price=1
weight=0
type=gear
desc=Useful for storing unique liquids found in dungeons.

[GrapplingHook]
price=2
weight=4
type=gear
desc=Best used attached to a rope and thrown, this can be helpful when crossing chasms or climbing walls.

[HolySymbol]
price=25
weight=0
type=tool
desc=A holy symbol serves as a focal point of worship. The form it takes depends upon the faith of the cleric. Holy symbols are necessary for spell preparation (prayer), as well as turning undead.

[Horseshoes]
price=1
weight=10
type=gear
desc=Horseshoes are important for the health of horses, and horses should have their shoes changed every 4 to 6 weeks. A farrier (person that shoes horses) makes sure the hoof is cleaned, trimmed, and that there are no health problems. In many communities, the farrier is also the blacksmith.

[InkJar]
price=8
weight=0.5
type=gear
desc=Writing ink is made of charcoal, various pigments, resins and waxes, and is stored in a small ceramic jar or tin sufficient for 50 pages of normal writing.

[IronSpikes]
price=1
weight=1
type=gear
desc=Useful for spiking doors closed (or spiking them open), and may be used as pitons.

[Ladder]
price=5
weight=2
type=gear
desc=Most adventurer ladders are rope ladders, which are two lengths of knotted rope strung with rungs, with a single line at the top for a hook. Ladders have an 850 lb capacity.

[Lantern]
price=5
weight=2
type=gear
desc=A lantern will provide light covering a 30' radius, dim light will extend 20' further. A lantern will consume a flask of oil in 18+1d6 turns.

[BullseyeLantern]
price=14
weight=3
type=gear
desc=A bullseye lantern is similar to a hooded lantern, only it is closed on all but one lensed side. This lamp projects light in a 30-foot cone, and includes a shutter.

[HoodedLantern]
price=8
weight=2
type=gear
desc=A hooded lantern has a shutter mechanism to close off the light and prevent it from being seen.

[Manacles]
price=6
weight=4
type=gear
desc=Padlock sold separately.

[ScrollCase]
price=1
weight=0.5
type=scroll
desc=A scroll case is a tubular oiled leather case used to carry maps, scrolls, or other paper items. The case will have a water-resistant cap which slides over the end and a loop to allow the case to be hung from a belt or bandolier. A standard scroll case can hold up to 10 sheets of paper, or a single scroll of up to seven spells.

[Mirror]
price=7
weight=0
type=gear
desc=A mirror is useful in a dungeon environment for many reasons. For instance, it is the only way to look at a medusa without being turned to stone. Mirrors are also useful for looking around corners, and can be used outdoors to send signals using reflected sunlight.

[Padlock]
price=12
weight=1
type=gear
desc=Used to lock doors with the appropriate latches, as well as manacles. Each padlock comes with its own key.

[Paper]
price=1
weight=0
type=gear
desc=Paper is necessary for writing letters and magic scrolls alike.

[10ftPole]
price=1
weight=10
type=gear
desc=Typical 10-foot poles are collapsing poles, consisting of ten 1-foot wood sections, and two metal end caps. Each piece is threaded so that the pieces can be combined to make a pole of any needed length. Collapsing poles can be combined for longer reach. 10ft poles are extremely useful items for triggering traps from a safe distance.

[Quill]
price=0.1
weight=0
type=gear
desc=A quill is dipped into ink to write on paper. A necessary tool to write letters and magic scrolls alike.

[Quiver]
price=1
weight=1
type=gear
desc=A quiver must be worn in order to hold arrows. Quivers hold up to 20 arrows or bolts. Sling bullets are typically held in belt pouches.

[Rations]
price=1.42
weight=2
type=food
desc=Standard dry rations consist of hard tack, hard cheese, dried fruit, nuts, and jerky, or any other food which will not "go bad" in less than a month. Dry rations are sold in quantities per-day.

[HempRope]
price=1
weight=5
type=gear
desc=Hemp rope is about a half-inch in diameter and has a breaking strength of 1,600 pounds. A safe working load for a rope is normally one-quarter of the breaking strength. One or more knots in a rope cut the breaking strength in half. This does not affect the safe working load because knots are figured into the listed one-quarter ratio.

[SilkRope]
price=10
weight=2
type=gear
desc=Silk rope is about 3/8 inch in diameter and has a breaking strength of 1,600 pounds, although it weighs considerably less than hemp rope. The notes regarding rope strength given for hemp rope apply here also.

[LargeSack]
price=1
weight=0
desc=Sacks are made from burlap, cotton or leather. Large sacks hold up to 4 cubic feet of volume and up to 40 pounds of weight.

[SmallSack]
price=0.5
weight=0
desc=Sacks are made from burlap, cotton or leather. Small sacks hold up to 2 cubic feet of volume and up to 20 pounds of weight.

[PackSaddle]
price=5
weight=15
type=gear
desc=Pack saddles have connections to hold boxes or panniers that are filled with merchant goods or extra supplies for a long journey. Pack saddles do not allow for riding the animal.

[RidingSaddle]
price=10
weight=35
type=gear
desc=Riding saddles are designed to fit the animal being ridden and has a seat to allow a person to comfortably ride.

[Saddlebags]
price=4
weight=7
type=gear
desc=Saddle bags are leather bags designed to fit over the back of a riding saddle and provide some storage on a ridden animal. The bags are tied to the saddle to prevent them from falling off. Saddle bags can hold up to 1 cubic foot of volume and up to 10 pounds.

[Spellbook]
price=4
weight=7
type=tool
desc=A spellbook is an essential feature of any arcane spellcaster's kit. This is where their spells and formulae are stored, and is used to prepare for spellcasting. If a spellbook is lost, the spellcaster can only remember the ReadMagic spell, and is unable to cast until they find (or write) a new spellbook.

[LargeTent]
price=25
weight=20
type=gear
desc=A large tent can offer shelter for up to ten men.

[SmallTent]
price=5
weight=10
type=gear
desc=A small tent is ideal for one, though two small-sized characters could share one.

[ThievesTools]
price=25
weight=1
type=tool
desc=Thieves' tools are required for the use of thief abilities such as opening locks and removing traps.

[Tinderbox]
price=3
weight=1
type=gear
desc=A tinderbox includes a flint and steel. The flint, which is a hardened piece of rock, is struck vigorously against a C-shaped piece of high-carbon steel. When done correctly, hot sparks will fly from the flint and steel into the tinder, hopefully starting a fire. The best tinder is a dried piece of prepared tinder fungus, carried in the tinderbox to keep it dry. Char cloth, hemp rope, or even very dry grass can substitute for the tinder fungus if not available. The time required to start a fire should be determined by the GM according to the prevailing conditions, but under ideal conditions, starting a fire with a flint, steel and tinder takes 1 turn.

[Torch]
price=0.16
weight=0.16
type=gear
desc=A torch is normally fashioned out of a short wooden stick with tightly wrapped rags at one end that have been soaked in animal fat or paraffin to allow it to burn for extended periods of time. When lit, the burning wick sheds light over a 30 foot radius, with dim light extending about 20 feet further, and burns for 1d4+4 turns. Of course, a torch is also useful for setting flammable materials (such as cobwebs or oil) alight.

[Whetstone]
price=1
weight=1
type=gear
desc=A whetstone is used to maintain damaged edged weapons such as swords, daggers and axes.

[Whistle]
price=1
weight=0
type=gear
desc=A signal whistle is very loud, and will gain the attention of your allies from a great distance, but possibly others.

[Waterskin]
price=1
weight=2
type=food
desc=A waterskin is a container for drinking water or wine; though generally water is taken into a dungeon or wilderness environment. The standard waterskin holds one quart of liquid, which is the minimum amount required by a normal character in a single day. If adventuring in the desert or other hot, dry areas, a character may need as much as ten times this amount. Note that the 2 pound weight is for a full skin.

[WinterBlanket]
price=1
weight=3
type=gear
desc=A large, quilted blanket used for cover from the cold. Also useful for covering a horse - if used this way, typically a horse hood is cut into the blanket that covers the ears and jowls (but not the eyes) of the horse to prevent it from being spooked.

[Arrow]
price=0.2
weight=0
type=gear
desc=Ammunition for bows such as Shortbow and Longbow.

[Bolt]
price=0.4
weight=0
type=gear
desc=Ammunition for crossbows such as LightXbow and HeavyXbow.

[Bullet]
price=0.1
weight=0
type=gear
desc=Ammunition for Slings.

[MessKit]
price=8
weight=2
type=gear
desc=A mess kit includes the essential utensils for eating while camping. Most often these consist of a trencher (something between a bowl and a plate), spoon, knife, fork, and brass cup. 

[CookingSupplies]
price=3
weight=7
desc=Includes supplies needed for cooking on the road, including some basic sundries, common seasonings, smoking wood, and so on. These are sold per week.
type=gear

[IronPan]
price=0.8
size=M
weight=2
desc=Ideal for frying. Can also be used as a weapon, I suppose.
dmg=1d4
stat=str
type=bludgeoning

[IronPot]
price=0.5
weight=2
desc=Ideal for soup and stew.
type=gear

[TeaPot]
price=0.3
weight=2
desc=For tea or coffee.
type=gear

[SmokingPipe]
price=1
weight=0
desc=Considered a halfling essential. The pipe is hand sized or a little longer, and consists of a short tube with a bowl at the end which is filled with tobacco.
type=gear
 
[MagnifyingGlass]
price=100
weight=0
desc=A magnifying glass consists of a large lens held in a frame with a handle. A magnifying glass has a minimum of 5x magnification, and can be used to start fires using strong sunlight.
type=gear

[Crowbar]
price=2
weight=10
dmg=1d6
stat=str
size=M
type=bludgeoning
desc=A crowbar is a bar of iron that curves at one end in a kind of a hook shape. The end itself is flattened with a narrow split on the tip to help pull nails out of a board. The other end is flattened without a split to help pry open one piece of wood from another or force open a jammed or locked door, or heavy objects such a stone coffin lid. When forcing open a stuck door, a crowbar gives a -2 (a bonus of 2) on a Strength ability check. Can also be used as a weapon in a pinch.

[Pickaxe]
price=6
weight=4
dmg=1d6
stat=str
type=piercing
size=L
desc=Necessary for mining ores and gems. Can also be used as a weapon in a pinch.

[Bedroll]
price=6
weight=5
desc=Bedrolls are thinly-padded sleeping bags which include a pillow and can be rolled up and carried on one's back. Necessary for a good night's sleep.
type=gear

[Clairaudience]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion enables the drinker to hear sounds in another area through the ears of a living creature in that area, up to a maximum 60' away. This effect otherwise functions just as the spell Clairvoyance.

[Clairvoyance]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion grants the imbiber the effect of the Clairvoyance spell.

[ColdResistance]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion grants the imbiber the power of the spell ResistCold.

[ControlAnimal]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion functions like a control human potion, but affects only normal, non-magical animals.

[ControlDragon]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion functions like a control human potion, but affects only dragons.

[ControlGiant]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion functions like a control human potion, but affects only giants.

[ControlHuman]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion allows the drinker to charm any humanoid by gazing at it. The effect functions like the CharmPerson spell. If the charm is resisted, the drinker can attempt to charm up to two more targets before the potion's benefit is exhausted.

[ControlPlant]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion grants the drinker control over one or more plants or plant creatures within a 10' square area up to 50' away. Normal plants become animated, having a movement rate of 10', and obey the drinker's commands. If ordered to attack, only the largest plants can do any real harm, attacking with a +0 attack bonus and inflicting 1d4 points of damage per hit. Affected plant creatures (who fail to save vs. Spells) can understand the drinker, and behave as if under a CharmMonster spell.

[ControlUndead]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion grants the drinker command of 3d6 hit dice of undead monsters. A save vs. Spells is allowed to resist the effect. Mindless undead follow the drinker's commands exactly; free-willed undead act as if under a CharmPerson spell.

[Delusion]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This cursed potion will appear, if tested or analyzed, to be one of the other potions (other than poison). When imbibed, the drinker will briefly believe they have received the benefits of the "other" potion, but the illusion will be swiftly exposed... (GM adjudicates)

[Diminution]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion reduces the drinker and all items worn or carried to one-twelfth of their original height (so that a 6' tall character becomes 6" tall). The drinker's weight is divided by 1,728; this makes an armed warrior weigh less than 2.5 ounces. The affected creature cannot make an effect attack against any creature bigger than a house cat, but may be able to slip under doors or into cracks and has a 90 percent chance of moving about undetected (both in terms of sound and vision).

[FireResistance]
type=potion
cat=auto
weight=0.5
desc=This potion grants the imbiber the power of the spell ResistFire.

[Flying]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
desc=This potion grants the power of the spell Fly.

[GaseousForm]
type=potion
weight=0.5
cat=auto
